   "source": [
    "\n",
    "Les données athle sont constituées d'un relevé des records nationaux d'athletisme de 27 pays pour 9 épreuves de course, du 100m au marathon. Ré-utiliser le protocole ci-dessus pour interpréter ces données\n",
    "\n",
    "En utilisant les fonctions de l'exercice précédent, répondez aux questions suivantes :\n",
    "- Quels sont les pays qui se distinguent sur les courtes distances ?\n",
    "- Quels sont les pays qui se distinguent sur les longues distances ?\n",
    "- Quels sont les pays qui se distinguent sur les distances moyennes (typiquement 800m et 1500m) ?\n",
    "\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import sklearn\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 432x288 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "\n",
    "data_athle=pd.read_csv(\"data_athle.csv\",header=0,sep=\"\t\",decimal=\",\",index_col=0)\n",
    "ListCountries=list(data_athle.index)\n",
    "X_orig=data_athle.values\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "from sklearn.preprocessing import StandardScaler\n",
    "X = StandardScaler().fit_transform(X_orig)\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "from sklearn.decomposition import PCA\n",
    "pca = PCA()    #instancie l'objet qui va effectuer l'ACP\n",
    "pca.fit_transform(X)  # effectue l'ACP\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.plot(pca.explained_variance_ratio_,'+')\n",
    "plt.xlabel('Composante principale')\n",
    "plt.ylabel('\\% variance expliquee')\n",
    "plt.show()\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Nom des variables= ['100m', '200m', '400m', '800m', '1500m', '5000m', '10000m', 'SemiMarathon', 'Marathon']\n",
      "Composante 1= [0.16 0.21 0.3  0.26 0.36 0.4  0.38 0.41 0.41]   (explique 53.1 pourcents de la variabilite)\n",
      "Composante 2= [ 0.57  0.54  0.36  0.21 -0.11 -0.24 -0.3  -0.13 -0.15]   (explique 25.3 pourcents de la variabilite)\n",
      "Composante 3= [-0.17 -0.24 -0.01  0.74  0.47 -0.06 -0.15 -0.23 -0.25]   (explique 10.4 pourcents de la variabilite)\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "\n",
    "print(\"Nom des variables=\",list(data_athle.columns.values))\n",
    "print(\"Composante 1=\",np.round(pca.components_[0,:],2),\"  (explique \"+str(np.round(pca.explained_variance_ratio_[0]*100,1))+\" pourcents de la variabilite)\")\n",
    "print(\"Composante 2=\",np.round(pca.components_[1,:],2),\"  (explique \"+str(np.round(pca.explained_variance_ratio_[1]*100,1))+\" pourcents de la variabilite)\")\n",
    "print(\"Composante 3=\",np.round(pca.components_[2,:],2),\"  (explique \"+str(np.round(pca.explained_variance_ratio_[2]*100,1))+\" pourcents de la variabilite)\")\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "**Interprétation :**\n",
    "- La composante 1 met en avant les grandes distances\n",
    "- La composante 2 met en avant les courtes distances\n",
    "- La composante 3 met en avant les distances moyennes\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 432x288 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "ProjData=np.dot(X,pca.components_.transpose())\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.plot(ProjData[:,0],ProjData[:,1],'+')\n",
    "for i in range(ProjData.shape[0]):\n",
    "  plt.text(ProjData[i,0]+0.1, ProjData[i,1]+0.1, ListCountries[i])\n",
    "plt.xlabel('PC1')\n",
    "plt.ylabel('PC2')\n",
    "plt.show()\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 432x288 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "\n",
    "plt.plot(ProjData[:,0],ProjData[:,2],'+')\n",
    "for i in range(ProjData.shape[0]):\n",
    "  plt.text(ProjData[i,0]+0.1, ProjData[i,2]+0.1, ListCountries[i])\n",
    "plt.xlabel('PC1')\n",
    "plt.ylabel('PC3')\n",
    "plt.show()\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",

    "- Pays qui se distinguent sur les courtes distances :  Jamaique, USA \n",
    "- Pays qui se distinguent sur les longues distances : Kenya, Maroc, USA\n",
    "- Pays qui se distinguent sur les distances moyennes : Iran, Croatie \n"
   ]
